@cheddar  added UT for topN and fixed the comparator

@fjy yeah, groupBy test existed already but updated that to be run on multiple segments and merged instead of just one

currently it has tests for timeseries, topN, groupBy and select queries.

there is another pending optimization that i discussed with @cheddar  today, that is to cache the union estimates to avoid conversion multiple times due to multiple comparison calls in topN query processing. I will do that in a separate PR for 0.9.3 and this PR is only to fix regression and to be backported to 0.9.2 .
